# Workflow

Use `skills-seed workflow` to create or update durable task procedures.

Workflows are for repeatable processes such as release, deployment, migration, code generation, review, or multi-step validation. They are rendered into generated Skills so future agents can follow them.

## Purpose

`workflow` turns user guidance into structured workflow knowledge:

- Name and identity.
- Applicability.
- Ordered steps.
- Preconditions and validation.
- Project or workspace scope.

## Flags

- `--name`: workflow name. If omitted, the agent derives one from context.
- `--context`: workflow guidance text.
- `--overwrite`: replace an existing workflow with the same identity instead of merging.
- `--child`: in workspace mode, apply the workflow to one child project by ID or path.

## Inspect Existing Workflows

- List summaries: `skills-seed workflow show`
- List summaries as structured data: `skills-seed workflow show --format json`
- Inspect one workflow: `skills-seed workflow show <workflow-id> --format json`
- Inspect a child scope: `skills-seed workflow show --child backend --format json`

The list form is intentionally lightweight. Use the detail form when complete workflow content is needed.

## Use Cases

- Add release flow: `skills-seed workflow --name release --context "Before release, run tests, check config, build artifacts, tag, then smoke test"`
- Merge new guidance into existing deploy flow: `skills-seed workflow --name deploy --context "Also verify database migrations and rollback scripts"`
- Replace an existing flow: `skills-seed workflow --name deploy --context "Use only this new deployment process" --overwrite`
- Add child workflow in workspace mode: `skills-seed workflow --child backend --name deploy --context "Backend deployment process"`

## Merge Versus Overwrite

Default behavior merges guidance with an existing workflow of the same identity.

Use merge when:

- The old workflow remains mostly correct.
- The user says "also", "add", "supplement", or "include".

Use `--overwrite` when:

- The user says "replace", "rewrite", "only use this", or "the previous process is wrong".
- The old workflow should not influence future generated Skills.

## Name Selection

Use `--name` when the workflow identity matters:

- `release`
- `deploy`
- `migration`
- `api-change`
- `schema-update`

Omit `--name` only when it is acceptable for the agent to infer a name.

## Workspace Boundary

In workspace mode:

- Omit `--child` for workspace-level processes such as cross-project release or root CI workflow.
- Use `--child <id-or-path>` for child-specific workflows.
- A child workflow should not be stored as a workspace workflow unless it affects workspace routing or cross-project order.

## After Updating Workflows

Run `skills-seed generate skills` to render workflow references into generated Skill output.

Use `skills-seed sync` instead when the workflow update should be part of a broader learning/generation pass.
